invoice.additionalNote:
nspected RTU #1 ( BOH )
Found unit off due to not correct voltage to unit
Checked wiring and components 
Found L2 Leg of power has a substantial drop in power @ RTU
Went to Electrical panel checked voltage @ breaker - all 3 legs have 120v coming out - 
Was notified that a Electrical company came out already & tried tracing wire & unable to find the drop in voltage or bad wire - 
Wire is ran under unit & not excess able unless you have unit craned up. 
I recommend to have Electrician run new wires from Panel thru roof line to a box on the outside of RTU then run flex line to unit to provide power to ensure all wiring is good & abandon old wiring due to not being able to pin point issue in wiring 
Notified Beverly of situation

notes.description:
Team,
After much back and forth MAS is aware of the exact issue and what needs to be done to make it right.  Mike at MAS and their team have agreed that it was a deficiency from the install of the unit 18 months ago and will repair it even though the warranty period from the install has expired.  They will communicate with you in the next day or so when they will get it taken care of.

HELP! 

this is now a life safty concern, my pregnant server said she almost fainted because of how hot it is in the kitchen.
Two months with a non operational AC unit is not acceptable.

Burgarello Alarm has now been out to inspect there end of things, they said everything is fine on there end, just like SMUD (local electric company) and just like the electrician said. MAS doesn't think we need new wiring to the RTU 1. Please advise/help with the next steps from here. 
I informed MAS that while the electrician was here the heater was working but the AC will not cool to under 78 degrees even when set at 66 degrees.
At this point we have had MAS, SMUD, an electrician  and a fire alarm guy out here to look at an AC unit? HELP,
Thank you for your time,
Dan
